The paper discusses the development of sensorimotor intelligence in robotic systems through a new synaptic plasticity rule. This suggests a focus on neural networks and robotics, which are covered by cs.NE and cs.RO respectively. The paper also mentions self-learning systems and creativity, which are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the biological plausibility of the proposed mechanism, which suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
